{
  "texts": [
    "To evaluate the autonomy and cooperation ability of LLMbased agents, this paper conducts experiments across three representative tasks (Cabinet, Pack, and Sort) in RoCo (Mandi, Jain, and Song 2024) under four cooperation paradigms separately introduced in Section 3.3.",
    "There are multiple agents in each task, and each agent equips a candidate tool set consisting of eight to nine tools to cooperate in achieving the final target.",
    "This paper runs five independent episodes for each task.",
    "Within each episode, agents are allowed to finish the target (take action) in ten turns, with a maximum of five replanning opportunities.",
    "Re-planning opportunities simulate realistic iterative decision-making and enable LLM-based agents to adjust their tool selections based on environment feedback or the actions of other agents."
  ]
}